But more importantly, we need to understand that if we are evaluating `⌈α⌉f` at `Sum.inr ⟨R, oldWorld⟩`, then we are looking for all `w'` such that `relate ... α (Sum.inr ⟨R, oldWorld⟩) w'`. 

By the third part of `IH_a`, there are no such `w'` of the form `Sum.inl ()`. 

